'''DTU Roadrunners''' is a student driven project at the [[Technical University of Denmark]] competing in the [[Shell Eco-marathon]] races. The team participates in one or both of the two classes at Shell Eco-Marathon Europe: the UrbanConcept class and the Prototype class with the cars Dynamo and Innovator respectively. The team consists of 20 to 30 students. Project work in the course is based on the [[CDIO Initiative|CDIO]]-working form and students are thus responsible for the development, construction and operation of the vehicles.
